      "description": "Follie — The Anesthesia Reference App Built for Students and Clinicians\nPrep smarter. Study faster. Walk into every case with confidence.\nFollie puts a complete anesthesia toolkit in your pocket — built by a clinician who knows exactly what you need at the bedside and in the classroom.\nDRUG REFERENCE LIBRARY\nSearchable database of anesthetic agents — induction agents, volatiles, muscle relaxants, opioids, reversal agents, vasopressors, local anesthetics, and more. Every entry includes dosing ranges, onset and duration, contraindications, side effects, and clinical pearls.\nCLINICAL CALCULATORS\nBMI, ideal body weight, estimated blood volume, allowable blood loss, MAC, ETT sizing, fluid calculations (4-2-1 rule, deficit replacement), and emergence time estimation — all in one place.\n60+ QUICK REFERENCE CARDS\nCardiac, pulmonary, neuro, renal, hepatic, endocrine, hematologic, and psych comorbidities. Pediatric and OB anesthesia. Nerve blocks. Neuraxial techniques. Airway anatomy. ECG reference. TEG/ROTEM. Ventilator management. Positioning. Physics and gas laws. And more — all written in original, student-friendly language.\nEMERGENCY PROTOCOLS\nWeight-based emergency drug dosing for ACLS, PALS, BLS, malignant hyperthermia, bronchospasm, anaphylaxis, and local anesthetic toxicity (LAST). Fast access when seconds matter.\nCASE LOGGING\nTrack your clinical cases — procedure, anesthetic type, techniques, rotation, role, duration, and personal notes. Build your case log throughout your training.\nPREOP & SAFETY REFERENCES\nASA classification guide, preop medication hold/continue recommendations, NPO guidelines, ASRA neuraxial anticoagulation timing, and surgical antibiotic prophylaxis.\nWHO IT'S FOR\nAnesthesia students, residents, and practicing clinicians. Whether you're prepping for your first intubation or your thousandth, Follie has your back.\n\nBuilt with care by Attuned Labs LLC.\nQuestions or feedback? Reach us at attunedlabs@gmail.com\n\nLicensing Agreement (Apple): https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/\nIn-app terms of service: https://heyfollie.com/terms\nIn-app privacy policy: https://heyfollie.com/privacy\n\nDisclaimers:\n1: Follie is an educational reference tool and is not a substitute for professional medical judgment. Always consult a qualified healthcare provider or physician before making any clinical decisions. Content is for informational purposes only and should not be used as the sole basis for patient care.\n2. Anesthetic plan generation is included with purchase. Some tools and features may require a separate premium subscription in a future update.",
